<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1445,2010]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1769,1794]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is atypical with its short, compressed preatrial aedeagal paraphysis and blunt apex, short, membranous shaft, lateral basal teeth and elongate apophysis of the style. All other species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1297,1436,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[1297,1436,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Discolopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the aedeagal paraphysis elongated and rounded, the aedeagus lacking basal teeth and a short membranous shaft and the style apophysis shorter. Macrosetae of the subgenital plate are variable in length and distribution. Of the seven dissected males, one subgenital plate of one specimen had the macrosetae in the distal half, another specimen had macrosetae in both plates in the distal half, and five specimens had macrosetae in the distal 2/3 of the plate. In most specimens the macrosetae of one plate were longer than the macrosetae of the other plate. The subgenital plates in intact specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[609,759,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis box="[609,759,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[817,953,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colopeus">
<emphasis box="[817,953,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. colopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be distinguished. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antizomavorus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. antizomavorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[330,433,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis box="[330,433,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[486,634,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis box="[486,634,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected at Biesiesfontein, but only those on 
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1436,188,212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Antizoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miersiana">
<emphasis box="[1211,1436,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Antizoma miersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are included in the former. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[474,693,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis box="[474,693,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Discolopeus arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the short crown, and male and female genitalia. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[425,561,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colopeus">
<emphasis box="[425,561,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. colopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[618,768,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis box="[618,768,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar in colour, dimensions and the subgenital plate, but differ distinctly in the configuration of the aedeagus, but not the shape of valvifer 1 of the female. Sternite VII of five dissected females, associated with 
<emphasis box="[627,778,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<taxonomicName box="[627,774,332,356]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Antizoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miersiana">A. miersiana</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
are of two 
<typeStatus box="[909,971,333,357]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">types</typeStatus>
. Three females are as in 
<figureCitation box="[1255,1334,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1389,1411]" captionTargetBox="[162,1447,193,1338]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1447,193,1365]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2a–g. Discolopeus diacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp.; male and female genitalia; line drawing. Posterior abdominal apodeme; a. Anterior view; b. Dorsal view; Sternite VII, specimen localities; c. Biesiesfontein; d. Wiedouw; e. Bitterfontein; f. Rondekop; g. Nuwerus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626815/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
, and two females resemble the sternite VII of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[569,718,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis box="[569,718,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in 
<figureCitation box="[797,873,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1761,1783]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,215,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1445,215,1727]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1a–n. Discolopeus diacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawings. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus with tooth subapically and apically respectively, laterally; f, g. Aedeagus with tooth subapically and apically respectively, dorsally; h, i. Style, dorsally, specimen with subapical teeth on aedeagal shaft and apically on shaft respectively; j. Connective, posterior view; k. Connective, dorsally; l Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; m. Style and aedeagus, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626813/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<specimenCount box="[849,873,367,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="generic">1l</specimenCount>
</figureCitation>
. Distribution of this species is in 
<figureCitation box="[1259,1352,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1474]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19a–c. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Hyaenanche globosa near Vanrhynsdorp and one record near Citrusdal (red squares); b. Potential natural distribution of D. copeus sp.n. in the southwestern parts of South Africa, Western Cape Province; c. Point distributions of D. colopeus sp.n., D. lissus sp.n., D. tetracaenus sp.n., D. thigmacaenus sp.n., D. triacaenus sp.n. and D. viraktamathi sp.n. in Western, Northern and Eastern Cape Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626849/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Fig. 19c</figureCitation>
and its feeding plant in 
<figureCitation box="[333,425,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,194,1855]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 18a–f. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Galenia africana; b. D. diacaenus sp.n.; c. Diospyros austro-africana; d. Diospyros ramulosa; e. Potential natural distribution of D. arctus sp.n.; f. Antizoma miersiana in north western South Africa and southern Namibia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626847/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<specimenCount box="[385,425,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="generic">18f</specimenCount>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
